What is the response that should come forth from my heart?

22:08.080 --> 22:14.328
Well, since we're all just common people this morning, let's learn from the shepherds before we close, shall we?

22:14.769 --> 22:16.451
And notice what it says in verse 15.

22:17.152 --> 22:20.356
And it came to pass as the angels were gone away from them into heaven.

22:20.416 --> 22:28.146
The shepherd said one to another, let us now go even unto Bethlehem and see this thing which has come to pass

22:28.258 --> 22:30.361
which the Lord hath made known unto us.

22:30.942 --> 22:37.431
And they came with haste and found Mary and Joseph and the babe lying in a manger.

22:38.353 --> 22:41.818
Oh, here we see the angels having given their message and left.

22:42.659 --> 22:50.450
Now we see the shepherd standing there alone, having heard the greatest story ever told that the Messiah had come.

22:50.722 --> 22:56.711
Maybe they were a mile or two away from Bethlehem in those terraced hillsides tending to their flock.

22:56.891 --> 22:59.736
But now there was an urgency in their heart.

23:00.116 --> 23:03.321
Now there was an appreciation in their heart.

23:03.722 --> 23:08.288
And so the first response of these shepherds is our response as well.

23:08.749 --> 23:11.934
And that is that they pursued the Savior.

23:12.415 --> 23:14.838
They pursued the Savior.

23:15.199 --> 23:19.986
The Bible says in verse number 16, and they came with

23:20.130 --> 23:20.691
haste.

23:21.152 --> 23:24.797
Here the Bible teaches us that they left immediately.

23:25.118 --> 23:27.241
They wanted to see the Christ child.

23:27.582 --> 23:31.608
Hebrews 11 and 6, but without faith it is impossible to please him.

23:31.968 --> 23:40.021
For he that cometh to God must believe that he is, and that he is a rewarder of those that diligently seek him.

23:40.081 --> 23:42.665
Let me ask you a question this morning.

23:44.067 --> 23:48.594
When you came here this morning, what were you seeking?

23:51.490 --> 23:52.472
Who were you seeking?

23:54.435 --> 23:58.581
The shepherds pursued Jesus.

24:00.765 --> 24:14.446
Were you looking for a good service to some time at church or do we come here wanting to see the Lord, wanting to know Him more, wanting to find more about Jesus?

24:15.888 --> 24:19.474
They were pursuing the Lord.

24:19.618 --> 24:23.050
left immediately and they looked intentionally.

24:23.431 --> 24:31.538
The Bible tells us in verse number 15, the shepherd said one to another, let us go even unto Bethlehem and see this.

24:31.682 --> 24:33.143
which has come the past.

24:33.163 --> 24:38.288
They said, we've got to see this stable area, this manger.

24:38.688 --> 24:40.870
We've got to see Joseph and Mary.

24:40.910 --> 24:44.093
But most of all, we want to see Jesus.

24:44.193 --> 24:47.536
And the word here, see is more than a visible sight.

24:47.956 --> 24:49.377
It is to perceive.

24:49.798 --> 24:51.459
It is to understand.

24:51.759 --> 24:54.962
They wanted a greater understanding of Jesus.

24:55.222 --> 25:01.668
They wanted to know this child that would be born to die for their sin as the

25:01.648 --> 25:03.090
of the world.

25:03.330 --> 25:05.112
They wanted to perceive Him.

25:05.172 --> 25:08.375
And so the shepherds pursued the Savior.

25:08.415 --> 25:09.697
Can I encourage you today?

25:10.077 --> 25:17.625
Can I encourage you this Christmas morning to pursue and perceive the Lord Jesus Christ?

25:18.807 --> 25:20.368
Our family is like every other family.

25:20.388 --> 25:26.235
We're going to get our kids, our grandkids, and they're going to be looking at those presents and trying to figure out which one is theirs.

25:26.295 --> 25:29.298
And Terry has a great method for never letting them know.

25:31.330 --> 25:36.878
She puts the names of the reindeer on those packages, so the kids never know if they're rude off or blitzing.

25:36.898 --> 25:39.021
They never know who they are until Christmas morning.

25:40.223 --> 25:42.406
But they look at those gifts, they look at those lights.

25:44.008 --> 25:50.457
But I tell you what I enjoy most of all, dads, I enjoy opening the Bible of this chapter right here.

25:51.899 --> 25:56.786
And I enjoy reading Luke 2, and I enjoy talking about the Savior that came.

25:58.178 --> 26:01.042
And I tell our family sometimes how I got saved.

26:01.122 --> 26:04.827
And I tell them how Jesus came to provide salvation.

26:04.847 --> 26:09.734
And we talk about what it must have been like for Mary and Joseph.

26:09.754 --> 26:12.017
And you say, well, yeah, that's not how we do it.

26:12.077 --> 26:13.719
Our kids are just not that way.

26:13.899 --> 26:14.720
You know what I find?

26:15.061 --> 26:17.845
Children will respond to the leadership of a family.

26:20.288 --> 26:27.858
Because what I want them to see, and I want them to see the presence, I want them to see how much we love them.

26:28.706 --> 26:34.753
But more than I want our grandchildren to know how much I love them, I want them to know how much God loves them.

26:36.055 --> 26:37.396
I want them to perceive that.

26:38.497 --> 26:40.320
And the shepherds pursued Jesus.

26:41.401 --> 26:45.225
And many times people go to church, but they're not pursuing Jesus.

26:45.265 --> 26:47.788
They're not in awe of Jesus.

26:48.569 --> 26:52.594
And here we find these common men in awe of Jesus.

26:52.654 --> 26:53.515
They pursued him.

26:53.835 --> 26:56.018
And then notice finally they proclaimed him.

26:56.738 --> 27:05.975
The Bible says in verse 17, and when they had seen it, they made known abroad the saying which was told them concerning this child.

27:06.677 --> 27:10.784
I happen to believe that when someone is truly saved, it changes their life forever.

27:12.007 --> 27:13.730
It doesn't mean that someone's perfect.

27:14.271 --> 27:20.082
It doesn't mean that someone never has a trial, but it simply means that their life's

27:20.258 --> 27:22.525
message is different forever.

27:22.846 --> 27:24.872
You want to share what you know.

27:25.414 --> 27:28.082
You don't have to be a theological expert to do this.

27:28.102 --> 27:29.787
You just know something great.

27:29.807 --> 27:33.458
And I find that people tend to talk about what's important to them.

27:34.434 --> 27:43.652
And people talk about their grandkids, like I just did, and people talk about their favorite football team, and they talk about experiences, and flying planes, and jumping out of planes, and all these different things.

27:43.913 --> 27:44.995
And none of it's bad.

27:45.075 --> 27:46.939
It's fine to talk about those things.

27:46.999 --> 27:52.690
But wouldn't you suppose that if you had met the Messiah

27:52.834 --> 28:02.646
the Son of God, the Redeemer of the world, and if you had seen Him, and that is to perceive what it's all about, and God let you in on this big picture.

28:02.887 --> 28:14.722
Don't you suppose that you'd want to make that known abroad, and that if you had someone that was your partner or your friend or your relative, you'd want them to know also about Jesus Christ, right?

28:15.543 --> 28:21.330
You'd want to share Him with them, and here we see what our response should be.

28:22.114 --> 28:29.862
As we look at the shepherds, these common men, our response should be, Lord, I want to know you more.

28:29.882 --> 28:32.124
I want to see it.

28:32.725 --> 28:33.846
I want to perceive it.

28:34.046 --> 28:42.935
And Lord, I want to tell others, I want to make known abroad what you have done and the way that you have loved us.

28:43.656 --> 28:50.002
Albert Einstein said, he who can no longer pause to wonder is as good as dead.

28:51.138 --> 28:52.560
Can I encourage you this Christmas?

28:53.861 --> 28:57.064
Don't lose the wonder of it all.

28:58.506 --> 29:06.795
Don't get over the aw, the awesomeness of God coming down to us.

29:08.717 --> 29:13.863
Senator John McCain spent five and a half years as a prisoner of war in Vietnam back in the 1960s.

29:15.725 --> 29:20.530
During that time he was frequently tortured while he was kept in solitary confinement.

29:21.890 --> 29:28.057
He later wrote that his lowest point was Christmas Eve, 1969.

29:29.919 --> 29:36.687
That was the moment when he felt, for some reason, that he would never be released.

29:37.728 --> 29:50.162
Homesickness had taken a grip, and it was made worse when the Vietnamese captors played on that December 24th, the song, I'll be home for Christmas.

29:50.306 --> 29:52.489
over and over again on the PA system.

29:54.271 --> 29:59.979
As that song was being played, there was a soldier next to McCain by the name of Ernie Bruce.

30:00.960 --> 30:03.964
He was a Marine that had been in prison for four years already.

30:05.586 --> 30:13.597
And he began tapping out in a code known only to the POWs, this message.

30:14.759 --> 30:18.664
He said to McCain, we'll all be home for Christmas.

30:19.685 --> 30:20.306
God

30:20.482 --> 30:21.823
Bless America.

30:23.565 --> 30:39.602
McCain said those simple words of the hope of Christmas restored his heart, reminded him of his hope, and gave him the confidence that he would be home again someday.

30:40.704 --> 30:50.354
May I say to you this morning that the world still needs saving, that God began the process 2,000 years ago.

30:50.434 --> 31:00.916
and that people even today who could just hear the message of Christmas could find hope in Jesus Christ.

31:02.981 --> 31:05.586
And I don't know if you've ever thought of it.

31:06.402 --> 31:09.345
but we look at people, you look at your boss, boy, he's got it all.

31:09.365 --> 31:10.887
Look at that boat, look at that new car.

31:11.087 --> 31:12.889
Wow, look what she's wearing.

31:12.909 --> 31:23.261
Whoa, and we see people a little above us maybe in life, and we think, boy, they've got it all, but can I tell you that just like John McCain, they are in prison to their materialism.

31:23.482 --> 31:34.354
They are in prison to their idea of success, and they are unhappy and without hope and without true peace, because when you don't have Christ, you don't have peace.

31:36.162 --> 31:52.338
And the amazing truth of Jesus is that when you really see and understand who He is and what He's done, then the peace of God can come flooding into your soul and you'll know that your rescue is coming again.

